<% content_for :meta do %>
  <meta name="robots" content="noindex, nofollow">
<% end %>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-lg-8 offset-lg-2">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><small>Last updated: <%= Date.today.strftime("%B %d, %Y") %></small></p>

    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>
      Recipes is a personal recipe management application that helps you organize, save, and plan your meals.
      This privacy policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and your rights regarding your data.
    </p>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>

    <h3>Authentication Information</h3>
    <p>
      When you sign in with Google, we collect:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Your email address</li>
      <li>Your first and last name</li>
      <li>Your Google profile image</li>
      <li>IP addresses and timestamps of your sign-in activity</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Content You Create</h3>
    <p>
      We store the content you create and manage in the application:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Recipes (names, ingredients, instructions, tags, ratings)</li>
      <li>Photos you upload with your recipes</li>
      <li>Recipe ratings and preparation history</li>
      <li>Menu plans and shopping lists</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Technical Information</h3>
    <p>
      We automatically collect:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Session cookies for authentication</li>
      <li>Error logs for troubleshooting technical issues</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>
      We use your information solely to:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Authenticate your access to the application</li>
      <li>Store and display your recipes and related content</li>
      <li>Enable you to search, organize, and share recipes</li>
      <li>Maintain and improve the application's functionality</li>
      <li>Monitor and fix technical issues</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Information Sharing</h2>
    <p>
      We do not sell, rent, or share your personal information with third parties for marketing purposes.
      Your information is only shared in these limited circumstances:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> We use AWS S3 to store uploaded photos and Sentry for error tracking. These services may have access to data necessary to perform their functions.</li>
      <li><strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> We may disclose information if required by law or to protect our rights or the safety of others.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Public Recipes</h2>
    <p>
      Recipes you create may be visible to other users of the application. You control which recipes you add to your collection,
      and other users can view recipes in the "All Recipes" section.
    </p>

    <h2>Data Storage and Security</h2>
    <p>
      Your data is stored securely on servers hosted by Heroku (a Salesforce company).
      Photos are stored in AWS S3. We implement appropriate security measures to protect your information,
      but no method of electronic storage is 100% secure.
    </p>

    <h2>Your Rights and Choices</h2>
    <p>
      You have the right to:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Access your personal information</li>
      <li>Update or correct your information</li>
      <li>Delete recipes, photos, and other content you've created</li>
      <li>Request deletion of your account and associated data</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      To exercise these rights or for questions about your data, please contact us at <%= mail_to "privacy@lailrecipes.com" %>.
    </p>

    <h2>Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      We use essential cookies to maintain your login session and protect against security threats (CSRF protection).
      We do not use cookies for advertising or tracking purposes.
    </p>

    <h2>Third-Party Links</h2>
    <p>
      When you import recipes from external websites using our scraping feature, you may be directed to third-party sites.
      We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these external sites.
    </p>

    <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>
      This application is not directed to children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated revision date.
      Your continued use of the application after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
    </p>

    <h2>Google OAuth</h2>
    <p>
      This application uses Google OAuth for authentication. Your use of Google sign-in is subject to
      <%= link_to "Google's Privacy Policy", "https://policies.google.com/privacy", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener" %>.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact Us</h2>
    <p>
      If you have questions or concerns about this privacy policy, please contact us at <%= mail_to "privacy@lailrecipes.com" %>.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
